<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Trawma Siirjen:
[B]I guess it's all in our definition of uber then.  It is a subjective term.  To me, a guild with 10 epics is uber.  If that makes me a noob, so be it.  I'm not on an uberguild server, so I know little of such things.

I'd like to examine once again the issue of some players being excluded from ever getting their epic.

Let's look at step one of the epic quest.

"1)  A tussle with Lord Bergurgle. Not exceptionally difficult, but he is a rare spawn with a long timer. Clerics frequently spend dozens of hours at this camp."

OK, rare spawn with a long timer.

Step 1 assures that only the clerics with hours of time to dedicate to camping a spawn will ever complete it.

What if I said that this is unfair to the players who do not have hours on end to play a video game?

To me, this is the same type of complaint as, "This is unfair to those of us who do not have an uberguild to back us up."

Do you feel for those clerics that cannot complete Step 1?  I don't.

Now, on to Step 3.

"3) An attack on Ixiblat Fer- Ixiblat is a true epic mob, far more powerful than any pre-buffed God. Taking him down will require several groups of 50+ characters all working together. Ixiblat is a triggered spawn."

This is not fair to those of us who are guildless!  What if I have no friends in EQ?  What if everyone hates me?  I'll never get past Step 3.

Do you feel for the clerics who will never have the chance to complete Step 3?  I don't.

Your complaints revolve around the supposed fact that you must be in an uberguild to complete the quest.  (Then you say your guild has 2 cleric epics, but it's not an uberguild.   /boggle )

How are the complaints I've outlined above less valid than yours?

Do you believe that if a cleric has no friends in EQ, that he/she does not deserve the epic weapon?

The only issue I see being brought to light is this problem with the last part of the quest.  What about the previous steps of the quest that also serve to alientate many clerics?  Is this fair?  I think it's fair.

If you believe that those previous steps are fair to everyone, then I don't see how you can have a problem with the last step requiring an uberguild to complete.

I believe that you're not complaining about the previous steps because, FOR YOU, they were doable.  But, alas, you are in an uberguild.  Just apparently not uber enough to farm epic weapons for your clerics.  And I think that is fair, too.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
